Python Output (print)

print() sends text and values to the console.

- Strings: print("Hello")
- Numbers: print(42)
- Several values: print("Age:", 25) — print inserts spaces between items by default
- Same line: use end=" " (or another string) so the next print continues on that line

See also: https://www.w3schools.com/python/python_output.asp

